<div class="center"><br />Ready for the coming storm? Sit by the fire with us during our winter overnight in NH's White Mountains</div>
<p>Professor Tom Zeiler did indeed join us today. Lucky for him, we know his habits and plucked him from his ATLAS stoop.</p>
<p>Instead of heading up high, we stuck to the lowlands, spinning around <em>Boxing Boulder</em> at a steady clip.</p>
<p>Dave took off like a rocket on Baseline, only to overheat near the Cherryvale junction. He was forced to shed some layers. I was also overdressed, having my mind pre-occupied with the looming storm.</p>
<p>No matter, we had lots of laughs and even a few ideas along the way. Thanks, guys!</p>